id=\u0022ips_uid_4050_7\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022 style=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Snark\u003C/a\u003E, etc, I think it\u0027s safe to say we\u0027re seeing a \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002216426\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sal_vager\u003C/a\u003E tribute from all of our mods.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027d be right. Sal has been the heart of the moderation team for as long as I\u0027ve been a part of it (and likely long before that, too), there\u0027s not really a tribute large enough that we can give him.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-03T05:03:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith Sal heading out, are you guys going to want someone to replace him on the moderating side of things? He was... \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Eis \u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/em\u003Ea big part of this community.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DarkOwl57","CreatedById":161624,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-03T05:26:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone realizing that we\u0027re talking about sal in the past-tense? Almost like he died XD\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-03T05:34:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSal promoted me so several of us could split his former duties for the moment. We don\u0027t plan to take on any normal moderators right away, anyhow, since there\u0027s still the issue of the other language moderators to be dealt with.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-03T08:49:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223007633\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491197681\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002227914\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vanamonde\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Vanamonde said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSal promoted me so several of us could split his former duties for the moment. We don\u0027t plan to take on any normal moderators right away, anyhow, since there\u0027s still the issue of the other language moderators to be dealt with.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003EWell you know where I stand on the subject so all I can do is wish you good luck in the transition.\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-03T08:50:56Z\u0022 title=\u002204/03/2017 08:50  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 3, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by ZooNamedGames\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex_NL","CreatedById":58254,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-05T17:49:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI understand there are rules about necro-posting. (Please note I said I understand them, I do \u003Cstrong\u003Enot\u003C/strong\u003E agree with them. In my opinion the wrong side of the equation is being enforced.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe small \u003Cem\u003E\u0022This thread is quite old\u0022\u003C/em\u003E notification is an improvement but it does not nearly suffice. People do NOT see or read it. And if they do, they clearly do not care. \u003Cstrong\u003EWHY\u003C/strong\u003E is there still no big bold pop-up slamming the necro-poster in the face reminding him of the fact he is about to raise the dead? A big fat notification that \u003Cstrong\u003Emust\u003C/strong\u003E be acknowledged before the post can actually be made. And don\u0027t say it\u0027s not possible because it is. A system like this is already being used for moderator warnings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-05T17:52:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223010651\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491414563\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258254\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tex_NL\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Tex_NL said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI understand there are rules about necro-posting. (Please note I said I understand them, I do \u003Cstrong\u003Enot\u003C/strong\u003E agree with them. In my opinion the wrong side of the equation is being enforced.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe small \u003Cem\u003E\u0022This thread is quite old\u0022\u003C/em\u003E notification is an improvement but it does not nearly suffice. People do NOT see or read it. And if they do, they clearly do not care. \u003Cstrong\u003EWHY\u003C/strong\u003E is there still no big bold pop-up slamming the necro-poster in the face reminding him of the fact he is about to raise the dead? A big fat notification that \u003Cstrong\u003Emust\u003C/strong\u003E be acknowledged before the post can actually be made. And don\u0027t say it\u0027s not possible because it is. A system like this is already being used for moderator warnings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI ignored that on a thread of mine dedicated to graphics. I do not get requests to do graphics much anymore, but when I do, I do not want them scattered all over the forum. Really, I think it ought to depend on what the nature of the thread is, to be honest. A depreciated thread whose creator is no longer active on the forum probably would benefit from such a system as described by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/58254-tex_nl/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002258254\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/58254-tex_nl/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Tex_NL\u003C/a\u003E...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex_NL","CreatedById":58254,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-05T17:57:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223010657\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491414751\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022adsii1970\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, adsii1970 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI ignored that on a thread of mine dedicated to graphics. I do not get requests to do graphics much anymore, but when I do, I do not want them scattered all over the forum. Really, I think it ought to depend on what the nature of the thread is, to be honest. A depreciated thread whose creator is no longer active on the forum probably would benefit from such a system as described by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/58254-tex_nl/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002258254\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/58254-tex_nl/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Tex_NL\u003C/a\u003E...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExactly. I don\u0027t mind threads being re-opened for a good reason. But not to answer a three year old random question that has been answered five times already in the first six replies. Most of the time the \u0027new\u0027 answer is wrong any way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-05T17:57:58Z\u0022 title=\u002204/05/2017 05:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 5, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Tex_NL\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"monstah","CreatedById":95210,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-05T18:02:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223010651\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491414563\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258254\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tex_NL\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Tex_NL said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EWHY\u003C/strong\u003E is there still no big bold pop-up slamming the necro-poster in the face reminding him of the fact he is about to raise the dead?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause posting on an old thread is not an inherently bad thing to do, and definitely not slam-in-the-face-worthy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-05T18:07:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/58254-tex_nl/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002258254\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/58254-tex_nl/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Tex_NL\u003C/a\u003E: I understand that. I even think we\u0027ve had this conversation before... or at least it seems vaguely familiar. Anyhow, you\u0027re right. Now I am not a rocket scientist or a physicist, but I do know which end of the rocket goes up... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E One of the things that bothers me is the change occurring in the forum - there seems to be a lack of respect between console players and PC players. I don\u0027t think there needs to be two separate forums. And there also has to be some sort of \u0022peer check\u0022 - do research and experimentation before posting \u0022advice.\u0022 Some of what you\u0027ve described (and again I should emphasis very little of it) comes from the differing strategies in console and PC. KSP should have never been offered as a console game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-05T18:28:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223010676\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491415340\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002295210\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022monstah\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n28 minutes ago, monstah said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause posting on an old thread is not an inherently bad thing to do, and definitely not slam-in-the-face-worthy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust to expand on monstah\u0027s comment:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot only is posting on an old thread not inherently bad, but it\u0027s a self-correcting problem.\u00A0 If someone \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Edoes\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E cluelessly necro a thread for no great reason, it\u0027s quickly and easily dealt with.\u00A0 Whoever notices it, just \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Ereport the post\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E and otherwise do nothing.\u00A0 Especially don\u0027t make an angry post in the thread complaining about it or ridiculing the poster.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are good reasons not to post something yourself.\u00A0 Because,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nit\u0027s rude\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nit\u0027s counterproductive\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nit accomplishes nothing\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nmost importantly, \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Eit\u0027s not your place to tell anyone what they shouldn\u0027t be doing\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E.\u00A0 (See \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/guidelines/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Eforum rules\u003C/a\u003E 2.4.b and 3.2.)\u00A0 Even if you\u0027re right.\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nReporting the post (ideally, with an explanatory note) raises it to the moderators\u0027 attention.\u00A0 Then we can decide what to do, if anything.\u00A0 It\u0027s our \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Ejob\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe may decide that it\u0027s a \u0022valid necro\u0022 (e.g. for a topic that\u0027s still relevant), and no action is required.\u00A0 Or we may agree with you that it\u0027s uncalled for, in which case a fairly common response is for the moderator to respond in-thread and then lock it to prevent further confusion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s quick, it\u0027s easy, it solves the problem permanently for that thread whenever it comes up... and \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Eit doesn\u0027t actually happen all that often\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E.\u00A0 Bear in mind that since we\u0027re moderators, we see \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Eall\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E the problematic necros (since they generally get reported to us)-- as a regular forum user, you may not.\u00A0 I can tell you that the little \u0022this is old, are you sure you want to post?\u0022 banner at the bottom really does work pretty well.\u00A0 Sure, it\u0027s not 100%, but the quantity of necro reports we received has dropped a \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Elot\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E since that banner went up.\u00A0 We get maybe one necro thread a week these days, tops.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Enot a bad problem\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E; it\u0027s a rare edge case, quickly and easily dealt with.\u00A0 No door-slamming required.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Benjamin Kerman","CreatedById":172792,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-06T04:26:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI changed my profile pic several days ago, and want to change it again as a tribute to sal, but am having a massive brain derp and can\u0027t remember how to do it. Can someone help direct me to the right place?\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:blush:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_embarrassed.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:blush:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dman979","CreatedById":123837,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-06T04:40:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClick on your name in the top right.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Profile\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClick the mountains in the left side of your profile, underneath your current picture.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDecide how you want to change your profile.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Save\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Benjamin Kerman","CreatedById":172792,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-07T02:54:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool, thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Benjamin Kerman","CreatedById":172792,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-07T20:02:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat do you have to do to get warning points?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-07T20:02:49Z\u0022 title=\u002204/07/2017 08:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 7, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Benjamin Kerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ENot that I want to find out...\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-07T20:40:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223013370\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491595350\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022172792\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Benjamin Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n35 minutes ago, Benjamin Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat do you have to do to get warning points?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBreak the rules severely or repeatedly enough for the mod team to feel a warning with no points is insufficient.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you would like some I\u0027m sure we could oblige you without needing to break any rules. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-07T22:42:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223013370\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491595350\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022172792\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Benjamin Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Benjamin Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat do you have to do to get warning points?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEngage me in a political debate on the forum... and we\u0027ll surely get warning points together...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand that\u0027s because the discussion of politics is forbidden under forum rule 2.2...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dman979","CreatedById":123837,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-07T23:01:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223013523\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491604920\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022adsii1970\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, adsii1970 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEngage me in a political debate on the forum... and we\u0027ll surely get warning points together...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNote- this is a bad idea to do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Benjamin Kerman","CreatedById":172792,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-07T23:37:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223013523\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491604920\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022adsii1970\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n54 minutes ago, adsii1970 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEngage me in a political debate on the forum... and we\u0027ll surely get warning points together...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand that\u0027s because the discussion of politics is forbidden under forum rule 2.2...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut what if I like all the governments?\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}